data.write

Interface DataWriter


  • public interface DataWriter
    Used when accessing the data layer for writing. To reference its method, use an instance of the class that implements this. this.writeData(AssetType, String, List) or new class().writeData(AssetType, String, List)
    See Also:
    DataReader, Write, WriteController

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      default void writeData(AssetType type, java.lang.String filename, java.util.List<java.lang.String> data)
      Write data to the specified file.

    • Method Detail

      • writeData

        default void writeData(AssetType type,
                       java.lang.String filename,
                       java.util.List<java.lang.String> data)
        Write data to the specified file. This does not create a new file, but only writes to files that already exists. The folder depends on the AssetType.
        Parameters:
        type - The type of data. AssetType
        filename - The name of the file. (Remember file extensions)
        data - The data to write.
        See Also:
        WriteController, Write
